  <h2>Try it: uncancelled vs cancelled fetch</h2>
  <div class="tone-junior"><p>Start a slow fetch then immediately click Cancel. "Broken" — the fetch completes and updates state anyway. "Fixed" — the fetch is aborted, no state update, no error.</p></div>
  <div class="tone-mid"><p>Open the Network panel. "Fixed" shows the request as "cancelled" with a strikethrough — the connection was actually dropped, not just ignored.</p></div>
  <div class="tone-staff"><p>Compare request duration in Network panel: cancelled requests in fixed mode terminate immediately. Broken mode requests run to completion, wasting bandwidth and triggering unnecessary state updates.</p></div>

